NW5 3EW  Let Girls Be Girls Campaign  Since 2011 we have been working in conjunction with Mumsnet, where this sensitive issue was raised as part of their ‘Let Girls be Girls’ campaign. We purposely ensure that our girls bras are not sold to specific ages but are sold in sizes.  They have been developed following customer feedback that girls want bras to protect their modesty at this sensitive age. The bras in question are not padded so as to enhance cleavage but are a smooth moulded shape to act as a modesty and comfort layer.  We conduct thorough tests and speak to our customers for their feedback and as such, will always investigate any claims against Matalan regarding the suitability of our products.    We take our commitment as a family business seriously, and Matalan is the only retailer in the UK to currently hold the Mumsnet Gold Award for being family friendly, an award we’ve held for the last three years.  Halloween Dress-Up Testing  At Matalan we are always listening to our customers and we asked parents whether they check the safety information labels before buying Halloween costumes or accessories for their children. Almost 80% of the people we asked said that they did. We wanted to let all of our customers know that we ensure all of our children's dress up products (including our Halloween dress-up range) to pass additional Flammability Testing.  This additional testing procedure means that our children's dress-up products go through rigorous testing before they make it onto our shelves and into your homes (or out and about while trick or treating!)
Our message this Halloween is to have fun by staying safe and playing safely. Make sure children know the risks of candles or naked flames, including sparklers and tea lights used in pumpkins and supervise them so that they play safely.  We also recommend using LED lights instead of candles as they offer the same spooky effect and are a great safe alternative that can be used every year.  Careers  The world of fashion never stands still. And neither does Matalan. For those with energy, spirit and drive there's never been a better time to join us.  Visit the Matalan Jobs site today.  Bangladesh Update  Please click the attached link to read our update on Bangladesh.  Bangladesh Update .  Ethical Sourcing Policy  At Matalan we take our responsibility to provide customers with clothing products that have been produced ethically very seriously. You'll  find the details of how we do this here...  Ethical Sourcing Policy .  Environmental Policy  At Matalan we recognise our responsibility to minimise the potential for causing harm to the environment and strives to sustain and improve the environment through the careful consideration of design, selection of materials and operational procedures. You'll  find the details of how we do this here...  Environmental Policy .  Become an Affiliate  The Matalan affiliate programme is a rewarding programme no matter what interests you, fashion for women or men, stuff for the home or school clothes for the kids. Take a  look at the benefits to the programme here...  Become an Affiliate .  Accessibility  The Matalan site to be accessible and usable by as many people as possible.  So if you have any difficulties in using our site, please let us know so that we can improve...  Accessibility .  Gift Vouchers  If you're stuck for ideas on what to buy then gift vouchers are a great option. They're available to buy all year round at your local store.  Business Update  Detail on our 2017 Gender Pay Gap can be found below.
